rComments: His voice is special; not rude special, nor he could be singing in an opera special. I mean his voice is special in the type of way that you don't notice it at first, but then it grows on you. I started this semester wanting to learn about microbiology, and I'm ending it wishing he starts a podcast where he reads to you by a fireplace.

Davidson is hilarious and makes lectures easier to get through. He explains concepts clearly and doesn't put an unreasonable amount of material on his slides like many other life science courses. His test questions can be on the harder end but still very reasonable and aligned with lecture content.

Even though I got a good grade A- i really did not like ProfDavidson as a lecturer. There are some pros and cons. The pros are, hes articulate and funny. The cons are, explanation of slides does not match the slide itself, because he doesnt make his own presentations, so he just reads off of them, which is a big flaw and his midterms are HARD
Lecture content is fine, tests are reasonable, overall an OK prof. The thing to watch out for is his voice; he has a very soothing, droning voice that can really numb your mind.
